descript.purpose: Create a country wide administrative boundary dataset based on PCO (Population Census Organisation) data.
descript.supplinf: This dataset fits to GAUL (Global Administrative Unit Layer) level 0 boundaries and holds the PCO (Population Census Organisation) administrative boundaries, level 4 This release covers KPK province completely, Sindh, Punjab and Balochistan flood affected districts only. Work is undergoing to cover the rest of the country

idinfo.accconst: Not for resale, freely available for the Humanitarian Community
idinfo.useconst: For use by the Humanitarian community. GAUL, OCHA and PCO are credited as the source of the data on any maps produced using this data.
idinfo.datacred: OCHA (Office for Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs), PCO (Population census Organisation), GAUL (Global Administrative Unit Layer).

srcinfo.srccontr: Population Census Organistation Office for Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs - Pakistan Global Administrative Unit Layer (FAO)

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Area of feature in internal units squared.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

cntaddr.addrtype: REQUIRED: The mailing and/or physical address for the organization or individual.
cntaddr.city: REQUIRED: The city of the address.
cntaddr.state: REQUIRED: The state or province of the address.
cntaddr.postal: REQUIRED: The ZIP or other postal code of the address.

cntinfo.cntvoice: REQUIRED: The telephone number by which individuals can speak to the organization or individual.

metainfo.metstdn: FGDC Content Standards for Digital Geospatial Metadata
